climbs.name: Nitrous oxide
climbs.fa: Dylan Carey, Stephen Danko, Matt Markell

content.description: First line at the new dental wall!  5 bolts and two anchor bolts. Find the shallow left facing corner in middle of the wall. First bolt is left of corner. Stay farther left for a little thinner slab moves. Can also look for big white and orange rock scar 15 feet up, route runs by it.Climb past rock scar, clip a few bolts, climb just right of small tree in middle of wall, slight slabby moves takes you to small ledge.  Look right to see a big spider cave. Climb left of corner past a chockstone to clip anchors. Bomber handjam above chockstone.
content.protection: Five bolts and two anchor bolts
content.location: There are two climber entrance trails to the base of the wall. If taking first trail, get to base of wall and walk 15 feet right to find the first bolt. If taking the entrance further down the creek bed, arrive at base and walk 15 feet to the left.

content.description: New wall as of oct 2020. Not as tall as the classic walls at med wall. May need some cleaning and traffic to spruce it up.  Will eventually have a few bolted routes, a kid friendly 5.1 route and maybe some multipitch practice because it has a few ledges.
